history.text: Hi, have you ever watched Maleficent? I haven
haven't*
No, not at all. I'm surprised to read it's based off of Sleeping Beauty.
With it being so dark, I never would've guessed.
Me too, I've never thought to see things from Maleficent's perspective since she's such an evil person.
But that's not the best Rotten Tomatoes score, I wonder how good the movie actually is.
Yeah, they can be pretty critical with scores. It's also hard to see Angelina Jolie play as a villian. She's usually the protagonist in other films.
Do you know of any other films directed by Robert Stromberg? I've never heard of him before.
I've never heard of him, but I know several of this cast. Like Elle Fanning
And I think I'd recognize Imelda Staunton if I saw her, the name sounds familiar.
Oh okay, I'm only aware of Ellie Fanning, besides Angelina Jolie.
Okay, this is starting to make more sense, at least a bit. Elle Fanning's character of Aurora, that's Sleeping Beauty's name.
I wonder if Elle plays Young Angie essentially.
But who are Diaval and Stefan?
I'm not sure. From the description, Stefan must be evil. Says he drugs her.
Okay, reading the whole thing Stefan wanted to be the successor but couldn't completely betray Maleficient.
But Maleficient didn't see it as that so she made the Moors kingdom evil as a result.
Sounds like it. And Diaval is like her right hand man and confidant.
Do you think Maleficent will send Diaval to kill Stefan?
I'm not clear on what kind of evil Maleficient is since it's still a kid's movie, but I'd say no because it sounds like she once cared for him.
I don't understand the curse. Who is cursed? Maleficient?
It's hard to say, either Maleficent or Aurora.
I don't see Knotgrass' character mentioned, so not sure about her either.
I think that Aurora is cursed. Maybe that is why Maleficent is watching over her before she turns 16?
Maybe. Interesting that she runs from her when she learns the truth. Wonder who she thought she was before that.
Yeah, Aurora already knew about the Moors but not about Maleficent's true identity? She really didn't want her to know.
So, she didn't know she was evil at all? That's interesting. I wouldn't think she could hide it
So, is Aurora the daughter of Stefan?
She ran to her father's castle. Stefan is reunited with his daughter, and then there's mention of Stefan's castle. That wasn't clear to me before if so.
I suppose but maybe Maleficent didn't act evil around Aurora.
Yeah, I'm also confused now.
It definitely seems like she didn't. Aurora viewed as her fairy godmother.
And I don't think Aurora is Maleficient's daughter, but her and Stefan were clearly childhood sweethearts.
Yeah, but it doesn't seem that Stefan cares for her anymore since he still plans to kill her.
I'm seeing why the ratings aren't great though
Angie was likely great in the role, but the story sounds a tad confusing
I agree, the plot is confusing.
Looks like Malefcient is the victor in the end.
As confusing as this sounds, kind of makes me want to watch to understand it better.
This sounds very mature for an animated movie.
It's animated? I thought it was live action...
Oh yes, I guess it is. It's just very costumey I guess.
But it's a kid's movie, right?
The description never specified if it was or not. Maybe PG-13?
Maybe. Even the reference to Frozen makes me think PG. But yeah, it just sounds more mature.
I'm going to see if it'll let me end the conversation.
I thought it would trigger on it's own, but doesn't seem to be.
